Shanxi or Shaanxi?  I see both spellings used within the same <a href="http://www.flickr.com/search/?w=25053835@N03&amp;q=Shaanxi">record</a>.  

I did find a <i>Wikipedia</i> reference of &quot;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanxi" rel="nofollow">Shanxi</a> &ndash; not to be confused with the neighboring province of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shaanxi" rel="nofollow">Shaanxi</a>.&quot;

<i>Wikipedia</i> then goes on to confuse me stating (under the heading of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shaanxi" rel="nofollow">&quot;Name&quot;</a>) &quot;if tone marks are not written, both Shaanxi and the neighbouring province of Shanxi, to the east of Shaanxi, should be spelled 'Shanxi' &quot;. 

Maybe this is one of those &quot;difference without a distinction&quot; things ;) ... and no matter how it's spelled, the photographs are wonderful!
